abstract: He pointed to the first caucuses of the 2020 election as further reason to reject removing a president exactly nine months before Election Day.
snippet: He pointed to the first caucuses of the 2020 election as further reason to reject removing a president exactly nine months before Election Day.
lead_paragraph: Jay Sekulow, President Trump’s personal lawyer, called for the Senate to reject articles of impeachment and “protect the Constitution and the separation of powers,” by allowing voters to deliver a verdict on the president’s conduct in an election year.
headline_main: ‘The answer is elections, not impeachment,’ Trump’s defense says.

abstract: U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Thursday defended President Donald Trump's response to American troops' being diagnosed with traumatic brain injuries from Iran's missile strike, saying he cared about the service members, as the number of service members diagnosed increased to 64.
snippet: U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Thursday defended President Donald Trump's response to American troops' being diagnosed with traumatic brain injuries from Iran's missile strike, saying he cared about the service members, as the number of serv...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Thursday defended President Donald Trump's response to American troops' being diagnosed with traumatic brain injuries from Iran's missile strike, saying he cared about the service members, as the number of service members diagnosed increased to 64.
headline_main: Pentagon Chief Defends Trump After Traumatic Brain Injury Comments
headline_print_headline: Pentagon Chief Defends Trump After Traumatic Brain Injury Comments

abstract: Patrick Philbin, the deputy White House counsel, upbraided the House.
snippet: Patrick Philbin, the deputy White House counsel, upbraided the House.
lead_paragraph: Taking aim at the second article of impeachment charging President Trump with obstruction of Congress, Patrick Philbin, the deputy White House counsel, upbraided the House for “jumping straight to the ultimate nuclear weapon of the Constitution.”
headline_main: House rushed to wield ‘the ultimate nuclear weapon of the Constitution,’ Trump’s defense argues.

abstract: “I think there’s plenty to talk about, and it’s an opportunity to move on,” Senator Roy Blunt said.
snippet: “I think there’s plenty to talk about, and it’s an opportunity to move on,” Senator Roy Blunt said.
lead_paragraph: “If I was him, I would avoid the subject,” said Senator Roy Blunt, Republican of Missouri. “But I have no idea.”

abstract: The screams echoed across Puerto Rico when Jennifer Lopez unfurled a feather cape representing the flag of the U.S. territory during the Super Bowl’s halftime show, a moment that many were still replaying and sharing on Monday.
snippet: The screams echoed across Puerto Rico when Jennifer Lopez unfurled a feather cape representing the flag of the U.S. territory during the Super Bowl’s halftime show, a moment that many were still replaying and sharing on Monday.
lead_paragraph: SAN JUAN — The screams echoed across Puerto Rico when Jennifer Lopez unfurled a feather cape representing the flag of the U.S. territory during the Super Bowl’s halftime show, a moment that many were still replaying and sharing on Monday.
headline_main: Puerto Ricans Thrilled by Flag Sighting in Super Bowl
headline_print_headline: Puerto Ricans Thrilled by Flag Sighting in Super Bowl

abstract: The denial was narrowly tailored in light of new disclosures.
snippet: The denial was narrowly tailored in light of new disclosures.
lead_paragraph: The key to the House’s abuse of power charge against President Trump has always been whether he conditioned official acts — nearly $400 million in military aid and a White House meeting for Ukraine’s leader — on investigations into his political rivals.
headline_main: Despite new evidence, Trump defense team again denies there was a quid pro quo.

abstract: The United Kingdom leaves the European Union at 2300 GMT on Friday, ending its 47-year membership of the world's biggest trading bloc.

lead_paragraph: LONDON — The United Kingdom leaves the European Union at 2300 GMT on Friday, ending its 47-year membership of the world's biggest trading bloc.
